During this Pandemic I have gone to this McDonald’s pretty much every single morning (and my app activity can literally vouch for this). Nearly every day that I go through the drive thru it is Agnes at the window taking my order.  Now, I will be moving to a different part of town and thus going to a new McDonalds. This morning while going through the Drive Thru I realized that made this my last morning with Agnes and immediately felt my heart drop.  Agnes is a light. In my brief encounters with her she completely lifts my mood. I’ve taken friends through the drive thru, seen her there, and literally had to explain to them how excellent this woman is. Not once has she messed my order up - but that isn’t even what makes her so fantastic.  What makes Agnes fantastic is her relentless positivity. Working in the drive thru is HARD. I’ve done it - I know. People are snappy, demanding, and can be hard to hear. This doesn’t shake Agnes. I have heard cars in front of me greet her with harsh attitudes and she still only uses kindness. I may not see her face because of the mask (which she is ALWAYS wearing properly), but her voice is smiling.  Your McDonalds is better because she is there. I might drive back just to see her 🤷‍♀️  Thank you, Agnes. Small gestures of kindness can mean everything - and yours have meant a lot to me. Please keep the good energy wherever you go.
